"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-06-20-use-african-championship-as-olympic-rehearsal-sports-minister-enoh-to-nigerian-athletes\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The Honourable Minister of Sports Development, Senator John Owan Enoh, has urged Nigerian athletes to treat the upcoming African Championship in Cameroon as a perfect rehearsal for the Olympic Games in Paris later this year.  This was disclosed in a statement by Diana-Mary Nsan, Senior Assistance on Media to the Minister of Sports Development, on Thursday.  Enoh stated this following the Athletics Federation of Nigeria's AFN, announcement of a formidable list of 40 athletes that will represent the country at the African Championships in Douala.  Among the standout names are Tobi Amusan, Favour Ofili, Chukwuebuka Enekwechi, and Chidi Okezie, some of Nigeria's biggest stars heading to the competition.  The Minister emphasized the importance of this championship as a precursor to the Olympics, highlighting its role in preparing athletes for podium success at the world's biggest sporting event in Paris.  \\\"The African Athletics Championship should serve as a dress rehearsal for the Olympics,\\\" Enoh stated.  \\\"I charge all our flag bearers to represent the green and white flag with pride and aim to bring back the first position trophy at the end of the tournament.\\\"  He also advised the athletes to be cautious about their diet and hydration, noting the significance of this Olympic year and the heightened scrutiny they will face.  CAF to make 2024 WAFCON, 2025 AFCON announcements Friday  Transfer: We have to wait - Agent on Osimhen's next destination  PDP Rep, Etteh backs Gov Eno's endorsement of Tinubu for 2027  Alleged 'demotion' of Enoh to junior minister angers Cross River radio callers  Libya: You have gone through near-death experience - Sports Minister, Enoh tells Super Eagles  AFCON 2025 qualifier: Sports Minister Enoh praises Super Eagles duo after win over Libya  AFCON 2025 qualifier: Do not undermine Libya - Sports Minister, Enoh warns Super Eagles  Super Eagles: Labbadia walking out on NFF very embarrassing - Sports Minister, Enoh  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"